            . I am an officer of the Thames Police. I saw the prisoner in company with another person, between six and seven o'clock in the evening of the 14th of October, in <placeName id="t18251027-56-crimeloc310">Ratcliffe-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18251027-56-crimeloc310" type="placeName" value="Ratcliffe-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18251027-56-crimeloc310" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251027-56-off308 t18251027-56-crimeloc310"></join>. I watched them for an hour. I saw the prisoner take this flannel from the shop of Mr. Bass - he wrapped it up in a white apron, and ran away. I pursued and took hold of him - we both fell together; I still held him, and got him into a butcher's shop, where I handcuffed him.</p>
